Beginning
**************

QuickFormat is a disk formatter for the new operating system OS 2.x, it
thus has all the caracteristics of the new FileSystems without excluding
the old ones. You will wonder why another of these programs has been
written since there are many like it out there. Well, QuickFormat is not a
simple formatter since it also creates @{b}AutoBooting@{ub} disks...

Lets see what the functions are:
@{b}-Drive @{ub}		Lets you chose the drive to format.
		If you select a non-existent drive the program
		will send you an error message and will stop the
		formatting of the drive.

@{b}-Name @{ub}		Lets you chose the name of the disk.
		The program does not accept empty strings.

@{b}-Trashcan @{ub}	Lets you decide if you want to have the trashcan on
		the disk.

@{b}-Quick @{ub}		If this gadget is on, QuickFormat will format your
		disk in a quick way. @{b}Attention@{ub} if there are errors
		on the disk, they will not be found using this option.

@{b}-Install @{ub}	The strong point of the program!! If you select this
		@{"gadget" link Install}, after formatting the disk, QuickFornat
		will create the needed directories to create a Workbench
		disk!

@{b}-Format mode @{ub}	Lets you chose which filesystem to use on the disk.
		Nota Bene: the DCFFS option only works on Amigaswith
		OS 3.x.
@EndNode

