@Node "Install" "Install"

  @{b}Install@{ub}
The gadget 'Install' lets you create an autobooting disk with enough space
for your programs.
QuickFormat, once it formats and installs the disk, creates the standard
directories found on any Workbench disk (even if some are actually missing)
and then copies the necessary files. Some command files are then copied
into the S and L directories.
QuickFormat uses a configuration file (found in the SYS:S directory), which
you can change for your own needs.
@EndNode
